revisions.rev:
'''Jasmine Revolution''' may refer to: * the [[History of modern Tunisia#Rise to the Presidency|1987 rise to the presidency]] of Zine El Abidine Ben Ali * the [[Tunisian Revolution#Naming|2010-2011 Tunisian Revolution]] in which President Zine El Abidine Ben Ali was forced out of the presidency by popular protests, called "the Jasmine Revolution" by many media organisations, and which was the impetus of the Arab Spring ** hence, the [[Arab Spring]] itself * the [[2011 Chinese pro-democracy protests]] in the People's Republic of China that were inspired by the 2011 Tunisian Revolution and called a "Jasmine revolution" by some of the organisers
